title.narrative: Pastoralist Resiliency Improvement and Market Expansion (PRIME)

description.narrative: (Ethiopia): PRIME supports resilience among pastoral and agro-pastoral communities, and thus enhances prospects for long-term development through transformative and market facilitation. It focuses on livestock market system strengthening, natural resource management and climate change adaptation, livelihood diversification, enhanced innovation, increasing household decision making power of women, learning and knowledge management, and nutrition promotion. It supports youth through technical and financial skills to start businesses working closely with TVETs in urban centers. The activity also supports the establishment and strengthening of mobile and agent banking platform to offer loans, savings, and money transfer services such as MFIs, saving and credit groups and associations. It will continue to improve market systems and capture lessons learned and will undertake a comprehensive study on pastoral and agro pastoral development to contribute to National Pastoral Policy and Strategy Framework.
